00:01:35.000 --> 00:01:37.000
[Amit Varma]: The political scientist A.O. Hirschman

00:01:37.000 --> 00:01:39.000
[Amit Varma]: once said that citizens of democracies

00:01:39.000 --> 00:01:41.000
[Amit Varma]: have three ways to respond to injustice

00:01:41.000 --> 00:01:43.000
[Amit Varma]: by the state. We may leave,

00:01:43.000 --> 00:01:45.000
[Amit Varma]: complain or comply.

00:01:45.000 --> 00:01:47.000
[Amit Varma]: Well, the philosopher Jason Brennan argues

00:01:47.000 --> 00:01:49.000
[Amit Varma]: that there is a fourth option, to resist.

00:01:49.000 --> 00:01:51.000
[Amit Varma]: His latest book,

00:01:51.000 --> 00:01:53.000
[Amit Varma]: When All Else Fails, argues

00:01:53.000 --> 00:01:55.000
[Amit Varma]: that our right to self-defense and to

00:01:55.000 --> 00:01:57.000
[Amit Varma]: defend others, holds even

00:01:57.000 --> 00:01:59.000
[Amit Varma]: when it is the state that is the culprit.

00:01:59.000 --> 00:02:01.000
[Amit Varma]: There should be no special privileges

00:02:01.000 --> 00:02:03.000
[Amit Varma]: granted to the state. This is a powerful

00:02:03.000 --> 00:02:05.000
[Amit Varma]: and thought provoking book and Jason

